  "content": "Scientists in Brazil have transformed cocoa waste into a functional chocolate-infused honey packed with antioxidants and natural stimulants. Using ultrasound waves, they enhanced honey s ability to pull beneficial compounds from cocoa shells no synthetic solvents required. The process is considered green and sustainable, and the product could find its way into gourmet foods and cosmetics.",
